\b \cf0 1.0
\b0  
\b Introduction
\b0 \
There are 2 basic sides to the TX Modular System, the 
\b System
\b0  itself and the 
\b Interface
\b0 .\
The 
\b System
\b0  is all the modules and channels which actually make and process the sounds. \
The 
\b Interface
\b0  is a customisable user interface on a set of screens that control the System.\
20 screens can be customised with 
\b Widgets
\b0  - such as sliders, knobs, buttons, number boxes, popups and text boxes. These widgets can control any of the modules or channels within the system. For example: buttons to start and stop sequencers, sliders or knobs to change volume levels, popups to change synthesiser waveforms.\
It might be easier to build a system first before designing the interface for it - of course, both can be changed again later.\
