\b \cf0 3.0 Design Interface window
\b0 \
This window is for adding widgets and designing the layout of interface screens. \
All widgets are shown inside boxes - the currently selected widget(s) will be in a red box, all the others will be in a black box. \
Each widget has a unique ID number beginning with a W which is written in red inside its box.\
Near the top of the screen is a row of controls used for this screen:\

\b Screen no
\b0  - of currently displayed screen (Screen 1-20)\

\b Grid size
\b0  - this is the number of pixels in each box of the grid which widgets are placed on. The default grid size is 10 (pixels).\

\b Add widget
\b0  - button and popup (yellow) to select which type of widget will be added.\

\b Width
\b0  & 
\b Height
\b0  - of widget to be added.\

\b Show GUI Properties
\b0  - opens the 
\b GUI Properties
\b0  floating window when selected. (See below)\

\b Delete selected widgets
\b0  - button to delete currently selected widgets (shown with red boxes around them)\

\b Clipboards
\b0  - these are places to store numbers when you are building a system. You can copy a number between the clipboards and any number box by dragging with the Apple/Command key pressed - you will see a blue symbol labelled" float" when you are dragging the value. \

\b Note:
\b0  
\i (as displayed on screen)
\i0  - Click on a single widget and grab its corners to change its size. Use Shift key with mouse clicks to add to group of currently selected widgets. Use Command key with mouse drag to add a widget from the yellow popup menu above, or to clone currently selected widgets. \
