This window is for changing the look of the widgets and what they control in the system.\
It is optionally displayed whenever the 
\b Design Interface 
\b0 window is selected if it has 
\b Show GUI Properties 
\b0 selected.\
The screen and widget displayed will change depending on what widget is currently selected in the Design Interface window.\
At the top of the window, in the 
\b Current screen
\b0  section, you can select the screen number, give the screen a name.\
The "
\b Copy or load another screen
\b0 " popup allows you to copy widgets from another screen as well as to load or save the current screen to a file.\

\b Screen image
\b0  adds a background image to the Interface screen (with various image modes for stretching and tiling).\

\b Screen colour
\b0  can be set using the colour picker, choosing a preset or by setting Red/Green/Blue/Alpha values. The alpha value is for transparency, with 0(minimum) being totally transparent, and 255 (maximum) being totally opaque.\
