\b \cf0 Action settings
\b0 : Actions are commands or instructions for any modules in the system. 10 actions can be set.\
Examples of actions include: changing the settings of any modules in the system, triggering notes to play, starting and stopping sequencers. \
There are 3 columns for the actions:\

\b Module 
\b0 - the module that will be instructed to carry out an action. \
(
\i\b Note
\i0\b0  - the first module shown is "System" where actions such as "Sync start" can be found.)\

\b Action 
\b0 - the action to be carried out when the button is pressed. Each module has different actions that can be carried out, so the options given will change depending on the module chosen.\

\b Value settings 
\b0 - settings that are relevant to the action: these are given in the name of the action. \
For example a Wave Synth module has an action called "Play note: midi note + velocity + gate time". The name indicates that values need to be set for midi note, velocity and gate time.\
Some actions don't require any value settings. For example, the Step Sequencer has an action called "Start Sequencer" which doesn't require any value settings since it simply starts the sequencer.\
