\b Parameter update settings
\b0 : parameters of up to 5 modules or channels in the system which the widget will be update. \
There are 5 rows for the settings each with 3 columns:\

\b Module 
\b0 - the system, module or channel that will be updated.\

\b Parameter to update 
\b0 - the parameter to be updated when the widget is edited. Each module has different parameters that can be edited, so the options given will change depending on the module chosen.\

\b Extra parameter settings 
\b0 - extra settings that are relevant to the parameter; these are shown in the name of the action.\
For example a Step Sequencer module has a parameter called "set Group Note: value, group". The name shows that as well as the value of the note being updated by the widget, an extra parameter needs to be set for the group to be updated. \

\b Note: 
\b0 The parameter in the 
\i\b first row
\i0\b0  of the "parameter to update" column will determine the 
\b range
\b0  of possible values that the widget can have. \
Whenever the widget is displayed, it will show the current value of the parameter in the 
\i\b first row
\i0\b0  of the "parameter to update" column. \
This means that even if there are parameter settings in the other 4 rows, the widget will show only the value of the parameter in the first row.\
This is necessary because only 1 can be "in charge" in case of conflicts. \
When the value of the widget changes (e.g. when a slider is moved), it will send its value to all parameter settings in each of the 5 rows, apart from empty ones.\
See section 
\b 6.4 
\b0 below to see how "unmapped" module parameters can be used so that single widget can control multiple parameters with different parameter input ranges.\
